WEBVTT

00:03.214 --> 00:04.795
Meredith:
They say love knows no bounds.

00:04.795 --> 00:06.467
I don't know about that.

00:06.467 --> 00:08.259
I feel like I've seen
the bounds

00:08.259 --> 00:10.131
and pushed them
a couple of times.

00:10.131 --> 00:13.054
-It's gonna rain.
-It's not gonna rain.

00:13.054 --> 00:14.895
Told her to have
the reception indoors.

00:14.895 --> 00:16.807
This wedding is doomed
even if it happens

00:16.807 --> 00:18.559
because it's definitely
going to rain.

00:18.559 --> 00:21.021
You want it to rain.
You are willing it to rain.

00:21.021 --> 00:23.484
I am not
willing it to rain.

00:23.484 --> 00:27.238
She's just so full
of feelings all the time.

00:27.238 --> 00:29.150
Why can't she just
cram them down

00:29.150 --> 00:30.781
and shut up
like everybody else?

00:30.781 --> 00:32.783
You can't expect
her to be Cristina.

00:32.783 --> 00:33.744
Exactly my point.

00:33.744 --> 00:35.416
She's definitely
not Cristina.

00:35.416 --> 00:36.497
That's what I mean.

00:36.497 --> 00:40.161
Owen wants this?
Owen's marrying this?

00:40.161 --> 00:43.124
He said yes
when she asked.

00:43.124 --> 00:44.925
Jo still hasn't
given you a reason?

00:44.925 --> 00:46.467
I don't need a reason.

00:46.467 --> 00:48.879
She doesn't want to marry me.
I'm done. It's over.

00:48.879 --> 00:50.631
Maybe it's nobody's fault.

00:50.631 --> 00:53.634
Maybe you only get one.

00:53.634 --> 00:55.055
One what?

00:55.055 --> 00:57.638
Soul mate? Or true love?

00:59.890 --> 01:01.021
Well, then, who...

01:03.063 --> 01:05.065
Izzie?

01:05.065 --> 01:07.358
Alex, Izzie wasn't
your one true love.

01:07.358 --> 01:08.689
And even if she was --

01:08.689 --> 01:09.990
What was Derek?

01:09.990 --> 01:11.492
Are you telling me
that you think

01:11.492 --> 01:13.574
that's coming around again?

01:13.574 --> 01:14.905
[ Sighs ]

01:14.905 --> 01:16.497
That was different.

01:16.497 --> 01:17.698
How?

01:17.698 --> 01:18.789
[ Thunder rumbles ]

01:18.789 --> 01:20.791
Love definitely has bounds.

01:20.791 --> 01:22.623
I've seen where it ends.

01:22.623 --> 01:25.296
I told you
it was gonna rain.

01:25.296 --> 01:28.879
This wedding is doomed.

01:28.879 --> 01:30.341
[ Woman shouts indistinctly ]

01:31.882 --> 01:32.803
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:35.095 --> 01:38.769
Amelia:
Mom. Mom! Mother!

01:38.769 --> 01:41.352
I know I was engaged before.
I was there.

01:41.352 --> 01:42.813
No.

01:42.813 --> 01:45.065
I am sober.

01:45.065 --> 01:46.687
[ Voice breaking ]
Because we love each other.

01:46.687 --> 01:48.529
Because we didn't
see a reason to wait.

01:48.529 --> 01:50.030
Because people get hit by cars.

01:50.030 --> 01:51.862
We've been together for a year.
[ Sighs ]

01:51.862 --> 01:55.196
Yes, we broke up, and then we...

01:56.907 --> 01:57.998
So what if it has
been off and on?

01:57.998 --> 01:59.700
[ Sighs ]

01:59.700 --> 02:01.702
Oh, hey, don't let me forget
the rings, and I called the --

02:01.702 --> 02:02.703
Shh, shh. Shh.
What?

02:02.703 --> 02:04.004
I don't know, Mom...

02:04.004 --> 02:05.746
Amelia's mom.

02:05.746 --> 02:07.418
No one in the family
is coming to the wedding.

02:07.418 --> 02:08.709
...ex-daughter-in-law
What?

02:08.709 --> 02:11.512
and ask her permission
to live my life.

02:11.512 --> 02:13.674
[ Crying ] Because I do.

02:13.674 --> 02:15.346
I'm alone.

02:15.346 --> 02:17.428
If you don't come,
it is just me.

02:17.428 --> 02:18.759
Mom.

02:18.759 --> 02:21.852
Mommy, please,
I am getting married.

02:21.852 --> 02:22.723
[ Sniffles ]

02:22.723 --> 02:23.764
Fine. Yeah, no.

02:23.764 --> 02:26.687
Um...okay. I understand.

02:26.687 --> 02:28.148
[ Sighs ]

02:28.148 --> 02:30.531
Yeah, it's so good to know
that all of the best people

02:30.531 --> 02:31.732
in this family are dead.

02:31.732 --> 02:33.274
[ Cellphone beeps ]

02:33.274 --> 02:34.365
[ Crying ]

02:34.365 --> 02:36.907
Amelia, hey.

02:36.907 --> 02:38.989
[ Crying continues ]

02:41.622 --> 02:43.334
Rain is supposed
to be good luck.

02:43.334 --> 02:44.785
[ Thunder rumbles ]

02:44.785 --> 02:47.208
[ Crying continues ]

02:51.792 --> 02:53.924
Okay.
Hey, uh, do you want to
go over there together?

02:53.924 --> 02:55.135
Go over where?

02:55.135 --> 02:56.427
To the wedding.

02:56.427 --> 02:58.679
Do you want to drive
over together, or --

02:58.679 --> 03:01.562
Well, at this point, I don't
even know if I'm going.

03:01.562 --> 03:05.226
[ Grunts ] Trauma's strapped
for surgeons and residents.

03:05.226 --> 03:07.938
Blake is gone.
Wilson's off.

03:07.938 --> 03:09.270
You could always
put me back in.

03:09.270 --> 03:12.573
Don't.
Yeah, I know, I know.

03:12.573 --> 03:15.316
Still, if you're shorthanded,
mm, just makes sense.

03:15.316 --> 03:17.027
Ugh, good Lord.

03:17.027 --> 03:18.449
You're just like Tuck.

03:18.449 --> 03:20.200
I tell you no --
you keep pushing and pushing

03:20.200 --> 03:21.782
like it's gonna
change my mind.

03:21.782 --> 03:23.374
You don't think
four months is long enough

03:23.374 --> 03:24.375
for me to learn my lesson?

03:24.375 --> 03:25.826
On a six-month suspension?

03:25.826 --> 03:27.248
No, I don't.

03:27.248 --> 03:30.251
If you think
a scheduling glitch

03:30.251 --> 03:32.713
will suddenly make me
trust you again in an O.R. --

03:32.713 --> 03:33.924
Wait. "Trust me"?

03:33.924 --> 03:35.886
What do you mean "trust me"?

03:37.548 --> 03:38.469
[ Sighs ]

03:38.469 --> 03:39.550
No, no.

03:39.550 --> 03:41.221
I get that you needed
to discipline me,

03:41.221 --> 03:44.184
but you don't trust me
with patients?

03:44.184 --> 03:46.146
[ Sighs ]

03:48.018 --> 03:50.691
It was a grave
error in judgment.

03:50.691 --> 03:52.693
And you're gonna trust me
again in two more months?

03:52.693 --> 03:54.485
That's what it will take?

03:57.117 --> 04:00.120
Miranda, should
I be here at all?

04:00.120 --> 04:02.783
I'll see you
at the wedding.

04:02.783 --> 04:04.325
[ Footsteps ]

04:04.325 --> 04:06.246
[ Door opens, closes ]

04:06.246 --> 04:08.248
I don't feel good about
how quiet it is in there.

04:08.248 --> 04:09.540
[ Thunder rumbling ]
She's fine.

04:09.540 --> 04:11.422
You have no idea how many people
have locked themselves

04:11.422 --> 04:12.793
in that bathroom.

04:12.793 --> 04:14.545
They're always fine.

04:14.545 --> 04:17.758
I am serious, Mer.
I'm worried about her.

04:17.758 --> 04:19.470
This is her wedding day.

04:19.470 --> 04:21.882
It's supposed to be
the happiest day of her life,

04:21.882 --> 04:25.476
the -- the magic day,
the love day.

04:29.269 --> 04:31.732
Amelia, we're here
for you, okay?

04:31.732 --> 04:32.653
As long as it takes.

04:32.653 --> 04:33.894
20 more minutes

04:33.894 --> 04:36.357
and I'm ripping
the door off the hinges!

04:36.357 --> 04:39.450
Amelia,
stuff your feelings in!

04:40.531 --> 04:41.742
What?

04:41.742 --> 04:43.404
It's not my love day.
I have things to do.

04:43.404 --> 04:46.206
Okay. Where is she?
[ Sighs ] Oh, thank God.

04:46.206 --> 04:47.578
[ Knock on door ]

04:47.578 --> 04:49.370
Amelia,
open the door.

04:49.370 --> 04:51.412
Amelia?

04:55.336 --> 04:57.968
It doesn't matter.

04:57.968 --> 05:01.802
If they don't want
to be here, then...

05:01.802 --> 05:03.974
they shouldn't be.

05:03.974 --> 05:06.517
We don't want them.

05:06.517 --> 05:08.188
They don't get it,
and they don't have to.

05:08.188 --> 05:09.930
I do.

05:09.930 --> 05:14.274
And I'll be there.

05:14.274 --> 05:17.067
And the only one
I want there is you.

05:19.820 --> 05:21.492
[ Door creaks ]

05:21.492 --> 05:23.404
You're not supposed to
see me before the wedding.

05:23.404 --> 05:24.495
It's bad luck.

05:24.495 --> 05:28.078
I'll close my eyes.
I won't see a thing.

05:28.078 --> 05:29.540
[ Sighs ]

05:29.540 --> 05:32.082
Come out, Amelia.

05:32.082 --> 05:35.045
Come out and marry me.

05:35.045 --> 05:38.088
♪♪

05:52.733 --> 05:54.475
[ Sighs ] Okay.

05:54.475 --> 05:55.436
Mm.
Go.

05:55.436 --> 05:56.817
I will see you
at the church.

05:56.817 --> 05:58.108
[ Thunder rumbles ]

05:58.108 --> 06:01.111
I am an excellent
best man.

06:01.111 --> 06:04.244
[ Sighs ]

06:04.244 --> 06:06.246
[ Siren wails ]

06:06.246 --> 06:08.539
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
over P.A. system ]

06:08.539 --> 06:09.620
40-something male --

06:09.620 --> 06:11.832
multiple stab wounds
to the abdomen and arm.

06:11.832 --> 06:14.124
He broke into an elderly woman's
apartment and attacked her.

06:14.124 --> 06:15.836
Oh, for God's sake.

06:15.836 --> 06:17.047
And the lady fought the bastard
off with a carving knife.

06:17.047 --> 06:18.669
Damn, Gram!

06:18.669 --> 06:19.920
Man: ...being controlled
by an inflated pressure cuff.

06:19.920 --> 06:23.173
-Vitals are holding so far.
-Aah! I was boiling an egg.

06:23.173 --> 06:25.305
He scared me near to death.

06:25.305 --> 06:26.677
I bet.

06:26.677 --> 06:28.599
Must've come in through the --
through the window.

06:28.599 --> 06:30.851
Came up behind me
in my kitchen.

06:30.851 --> 06:32.933
So I just -- hyah!

06:32.933 --> 06:35.436
Yah-yah, yah-yah!

06:35.436 --> 06:37.317
-Pressure on that, Cross.
-I'm trying.

06:37.317 --> 06:38.899
[ Siren wailing ]
Oh, here, I got it.

06:38.899 --> 06:41.151
Is she -- Is she okay?

06:41.151 --> 06:42.863
How about you don't
talk about her?

06:42.863 --> 06:44.865
Yeah, you picked the wrong
grandma today, bud.

06:44.865 --> 06:47.658
She's my mother.

06:47.658 --> 06:48.909
[ Breathing heavily ]

06:48.909 --> 06:50.621
I take care of her.

06:50.621 --> 06:52.202
She has dementia.

06:52.202 --> 06:54.625
She didn't know it was me.

06:54.625 --> 06:55.836
She didn't know.

06:55.836 --> 06:57.628
[ Inhales sharply ]

06:57.628 --> 06:58.879
[ Grunting ]

06:58.879 --> 07:00.000
Jackson: It's all right.

07:00.000 --> 07:02.382
We'll need to get
you some X-rays.

07:02.382 --> 07:04.805
Can you move your thumb
for me?

07:04.805 --> 07:07.257
Where were you?

07:07.257 --> 07:09.930
I'm sorry?

07:09.930 --> 07:11.682
You left me all alone,

07:11.682 --> 07:14.855
and I had to --
You should've been there.

07:14.855 --> 07:18.689
You should've been there for me,
should've taken care of me.

07:18.689 --> 07:22.112
Louise, do you know
where you are?

07:22.112 --> 07:25.736
That's...
what a husband does.

07:27.407 --> 07:29.780
Okay.

07:29.780 --> 07:33.664
[ Crying ] Don't --
Don't -- Don't leave me.

07:33.664 --> 07:35.415
Don't leave.
Don't leave me.

07:35.415 --> 07:36.456
Oh, okay, all right.

07:36.456 --> 07:37.788
Don't leave me again.

07:37.788 --> 07:38.879
Please. Please.

07:38.879 --> 07:40.420
Okay.

07:40.420 --> 07:43.083
[ Thunder rumbling ]

07:54.895 --> 07:57.147
Let's make a baby.

07:57.147 --> 07:59.229
What?

07:59.229 --> 08:01.231
You said that
you wanted a baby,

08:01.231 --> 08:03.023
and you would make
an amazing dad.

08:03.023 --> 08:04.775
And that's what you're
worried about, right --

08:04.775 --> 08:05.656
that I'm not all in?

08:05.656 --> 08:06.697
But I am.

08:06.697 --> 08:09.530
And I love you.

08:09.530 --> 08:10.951
[ Rumbling continues ]

08:10.951 --> 08:14.034
Are you gonna tell me
why you won't marry me?

08:14.034 --> 08:17.998
I told you
that I love you...

08:17.998 --> 08:19.710
and that
I'm not going anywhere.

08:19.710 --> 08:22.252
So isn't that enough?
Can't that be enough for you?

08:25.335 --> 08:26.967
You know, I was with
Mer this morning,

08:26.967 --> 08:28.388
and I was thinking,
the two of us,

08:28.388 --> 08:29.429
we've been through hell.

08:29.429 --> 08:31.892
You know,
all kinds of drama --

08:31.892 --> 08:34.765
crazy family stuff,
we both almost died,

08:34.765 --> 08:36.266
losing people we love.

08:36.266 --> 08:38.058
No, y-you're not losing me.

08:38.058 --> 08:39.770
The point is, we grew up.

08:39.770 --> 08:41.521
Mer and I are grown up.

08:41.521 --> 08:43.944
We got through it.

08:43.944 --> 08:45.145
And hell is behind me.

08:45.145 --> 08:46.777
It's in my rearview mirror,
and I'm not going back.

08:46.777 --> 08:48.989
I'm done.
[ Sighs ]

08:48.989 --> 08:51.451
I'm not -- I'm not
some idiot kid anymore, Jo.

08:51.451 --> 08:53.533
I'm a man,
and I'm done with games.

08:53.533 --> 08:56.366
I'm done with with crazy.
I'm done with losing.

08:56.366 --> 08:58.619
I'm done with drama.

08:58.619 --> 09:00.330
I don't care
about your secrets

09:00.330 --> 09:02.212
and your excuses
and your drama.

09:02.212 --> 09:04.124
You know, I-I've had that.

09:04.124 --> 09:05.295
Alex, if we could just --

09:05.295 --> 09:08.258
I just said
I don't want to do this!

09:08.258 --> 09:11.511
I -- I have never
had one second

09:11.511 --> 09:13.223
of anything real
my entire life.

09:13.223 --> 09:14.595
I want truth.

09:14.595 --> 09:17.598
I want -- I want a wife
and a house and a family!

09:17.598 --> 09:20.811
Amelia and, uh, Owen's
wedding today -- I want that!

09:20.811 --> 09:22.312
[ Rumbling continues ]

09:22.312 --> 09:25.105
♪♪

09:42.753 --> 09:44.755
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
over P.A. system ]

09:44.755 --> 09:47.507
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

09:47.507 --> 09:49.670
Hey.
Hey.

09:49.670 --> 09:51.842
Surprised to see you here.

09:51.842 --> 09:53.884
I work here.

09:53.884 --> 09:56.056
Well, I just figured
you'd be at the wedding by now.

09:56.056 --> 09:59.099
♪♪

10:01.521 --> 10:04.274
So, um...do you
have some time

10:04.274 --> 10:07.067
before you have to
be at the church?

10:07.067 --> 10:08.568
Don't do that.

10:08.568 --> 10:11.401
Do what?

10:11.401 --> 10:12.572
Get any ideas.

10:12.572 --> 10:13.824
Don't get any ideas.

10:13.824 --> 10:15.035
There are no ideas
here for you.

10:15.035 --> 10:16.326
I don't have any ideas,
okay?

10:16.326 --> 10:17.788
This is --
I'm just making small talk.

10:17.788 --> 10:18.618
Okay, well, don't do that.

10:18.618 --> 10:19.870
Why not?

10:19.870 --> 10:21.451
Because I'm busy.
I'm working.

10:21.451 --> 10:22.582
Okay.
I'm busy.

10:22.582 --> 10:24.705
I'm working, too.

10:26.086 --> 10:27.457
I'm not trying to be mean.

10:27.457 --> 10:30.550
I just -- I don't want
you to get too attached.

10:30.550 --> 10:32.713
I have three children,
a big job.

10:32.713 --> 10:33.804
Okay, you jumped me.

10:33.804 --> 10:35.555
Okay, not that I minded.

10:35.555 --> 10:36.516
It was good.

10:36.516 --> 10:37.928
We had a good time.

10:37.928 --> 10:39.309
It was very good.

10:39.309 --> 10:41.021
I don't know about you, but that
was some of my best work.

10:41.021 --> 10:42.472
And in a car,
which is not easy.

10:42.472 --> 10:43.603
But now what?

10:43.603 --> 10:45.225
Now you think, what,
you're my sun and my moon,

10:45.225 --> 10:46.687
that all of a sudden

10:46.687 --> 10:48.689
I think that the stars
shine down on only you,

10:48.689 --> 10:50.230
that you touched me
and the heavens opened

10:50.230 --> 10:53.533
and I -- I'm blinded
by the angel that is you?

10:53.533 --> 10:57.117
I mean, you're good,
but nobody's that good.

10:57.117 --> 10:59.449
I did jump you, didn't I?

10:59.449 --> 11:01.371
Yeah. You did.

11:01.371 --> 11:03.283
[ Laughs ]

11:06.456 --> 11:08.839
Okay, well, point taken.
You are not after me.

11:08.839 --> 11:10.290
I'm not after you.

11:10.290 --> 11:12.753
We are friends

11:12.753 --> 11:14.464
who maybe have sex.

11:14.464 --> 11:16.136
We're friends
who had sex once.

11:16.136 --> 11:19.970
Uh, we are friends that had sex
four times in one night,

11:19.970 --> 11:22.973
but let's not get picky.

11:24.564 --> 11:26.016
[ Indistinct conversations ]

11:26.016 --> 11:27.938
[ Elevator bell dings ]

11:27.938 --> 11:29.269
[ Door closes ]

11:29.269 --> 11:31.231
[ Thunder rumbles ]

11:32.612 --> 11:33.774
Okay, yeah.

11:33.774 --> 11:35.275
So the tux is here,
shoes there.

11:35.275 --> 11:37.778
Um, is there anything
else you need?

11:37.778 --> 11:39.119
I'll be fine.
You're good?

11:39.119 --> 11:40.490
And did you
remember black socks?

11:40.490 --> 11:41.701
Uh...

11:41.701 --> 11:43.784
Ha, I knew it.

11:43.784 --> 11:45.325
You know,
thank God for you.

11:45.325 --> 11:47.748
This is why I had you
hold on to the rings.

11:47.748 --> 11:49.669
[ Chuckles ]
[ Thunder rumbling ]

11:49.669 --> 11:50.921
Thank God for me.

11:50.921 --> 11:53.093
[ Panting ]

11:53.093 --> 11:54.254
Oh.

11:54.254 --> 11:55.545
Hey, am I
the first one here?

11:55.545 --> 11:56.596
Do you have a car?
Why?

11:56.596 --> 11:57.547
Do you have a car?!

11:57.547 --> 11:59.599
Yes. Why?
Okay.

12:00.140 --> 12:02.763
Ugh, damn it.
[ Grunts ]

12:02.763 --> 12:03.723
[ Door opens ]

12:03.723 --> 12:04.895
Hey.
Hey.

12:04.895 --> 12:05.976
Uh, Amelia's next door.
[ Door closes ]

12:05.976 --> 12:07.557
You can go through
there if you want.

12:07.557 --> 12:09.399
Here.
Thanks.

12:09.399 --> 12:10.520
Big day today.

12:10.520 --> 12:11.611
[ Chuckles ]

12:11.611 --> 12:13.023
Big step.

12:13.023 --> 12:14.775
Mm-hmm.

12:14.775 --> 12:16.616
Really big step.

12:16.616 --> 12:18.238
[ Thunder rumbling ]

12:20.240 --> 12:21.912
Meredith, why do you
have a problem

12:21.912 --> 12:23.283
with me marrying
your sister?

12:23.283 --> 12:26.456
I don't,
but I'm responsible.

12:26.456 --> 12:29.579
I mean, he left her to me,
and she left you to me.

12:29.579 --> 12:31.501
[ Sighs ] I'm not
a piece of property

12:31.501 --> 12:34.374
for Cristina to just hand over
for safekeeping.

12:34.374 --> 12:37.137
I haven't told her.
Does she know?

12:37.137 --> 12:38.468
No.

12:38.468 --> 12:39.639
Don't you think
you should call her

12:39.639 --> 12:40.931
and tell her
before you do this?

12:40.931 --> 12:42.182
[ Scoffs ]
Why would I do that?

12:42.182 --> 12:43.974
She was
the love of your life.

12:43.974 --> 12:45.725
If it were me,
I would call Derek --

12:45.725 --> 12:48.518
I don't know -- just to see
if it came close to what we had.

12:48.518 --> 12:50.851
[ Rumbling continues ]

12:50.851 --> 12:52.562
Okay, look up for me.

12:55.485 --> 12:57.607
Amelia.

12:59.659 --> 13:02.162
This is your love day.

13:02.162 --> 13:04.034
It is a happy day.

13:04.034 --> 13:04.955
It's so happy.

13:04.955 --> 13:05.866
[ Sighs ]

13:05.866 --> 13:07.707
I'm happy.

13:07.707 --> 13:08.618
[ Sighs ]

13:08.618 --> 13:09.789
Amelia.

13:09.789 --> 13:11.832
Nothing.

13:14.374 --> 13:17.297
Derek was supposed to
walk me down the aisle.

13:17.297 --> 13:20.050
My dad's gone,
and he's always --

13:21.761 --> 13:25.055
He walked every one of
my sisters down the aisle.

13:25.055 --> 13:29.850
Well, I'm here, and Meredith
will be here any minute,

13:29.850 --> 13:32.232
and we will all be together.

13:32.232 --> 13:34.604
♪♪

13:37.357 --> 13:38.318
[ Thunder rumbles ]

13:38.318 --> 13:39.069
[ Sighs ]

13:39.069 --> 13:41.031
I left the rings...

13:41.902 --> 13:43.363
[ Door closes ]

13:43.363 --> 13:44.444
I don't remember
where I left the rings.

13:44.444 --> 13:45.866
[ Sighs ]

13:45.866 --> 13:47.537
Well, uh, they say
if you think out loud

13:47.537 --> 13:49.289
while you're looking for
something, you find it faster.

13:49.289 --> 13:50.210
Who says?

13:50.210 --> 13:52.162
Scientists...
who lose things.

13:52.162 --> 13:54.294
Okay. Okay. All right.

13:54.294 --> 13:56.836
I remember there was one point
that I went upstairs.

13:56.836 --> 13:57.587
[ Thunder crashes ]

13:57.587 --> 13:59.920
You okay?

13:59.920 --> 14:01.511
Yep. I'm fine.

14:01.511 --> 14:04.674
Uh, I went upstairs,
and Amelia was in the bathroom.

14:04.674 --> 14:05.805
And -- Okay.

14:05.805 --> 14:07.847
[ Thunder rumbling ]

14:12.642 --> 14:14.184
[ Door opens ]
Meredith: Hey. I'm here.

14:14.184 --> 14:15.896
Sorry I'm late.
[ Door closes ]

14:15.896 --> 14:18.148
I had two patients
I had to discharge,

14:18.148 --> 14:20.820
and Owen just
had cuff-link issues.

14:22.402 --> 14:25.195
Are you okay?

14:25.195 --> 14:27.327
Amelia?

14:27.327 --> 14:29.119
You should probably go.

14:29.119 --> 14:30.620
Where's Maggie?

14:30.620 --> 14:31.871
She's checking
on the weather.

14:31.871 --> 14:33.333
[ Thunder rumbling ]

14:33.333 --> 14:35.585
It's raining.
Didn't you notice?

14:35.585 --> 14:37.297
What's wrong?
What's happening?

14:37.297 --> 14:38.999
What can I do?

14:38.999 --> 14:41.591
What can you do?

14:41.591 --> 14:43.843
What can you do?

14:43.843 --> 14:46.216
[ Chuckles ] What --
That -- That is amazing.

14:46.216 --> 14:48.508
That is
an amazing question.

14:48.508 --> 14:50.720
What can you do?

14:50.720 --> 14:52.352
Amelia.

14:52.352 --> 14:55.315
Meredith,
I am flipping out here.

14:55.315 --> 14:58.108
I'm wearing a wedding gown.

14:58.108 --> 15:00.230
There is a good
and decent man in there

15:00.230 --> 15:03.153
who loves me and is
expecting to marry me,

15:03.153 --> 15:05.575
and I can't tell if I am
marrying because I love him back

15:05.575 --> 15:08.949
or because I just ran here
and picked up a scalpel

15:08.949 --> 15:11.411
and slipped into
this Shepherd skin.

15:11.411 --> 15:13.333
And maybe it is right,
and maybe it's not,

15:13.333 --> 15:14.704
but I don't know,

15:14.704 --> 15:16.416
and I am marrying
Cristina's husband.

15:16.416 --> 15:18.498
I know what you think
about that.

15:18.498 --> 15:20.540
And I don't know
what I'm doing.

15:20.540 --> 15:22.632
And there is no one
here with me.

15:22.632 --> 15:25.635
There is no one here
to tell me to quit

15:25.635 --> 15:28.718
or get me down
the aisle or j-- help me.

15:28.718 --> 15:32.102
That is Derek's job,
and Derek is dead.

15:32.102 --> 15:34.644
And all I have is Maggie,

15:34.644 --> 15:38.688
and Maggie is full of sunshine
and candy and hope,

15:38.688 --> 15:41.231
and every time I try to tell her
that the world is on fire,

15:41.231 --> 15:42.482
she hands me
a marshmallow to roast,

15:42.482 --> 15:44.524
so that just leaves you.

15:44.524 --> 15:49.119
And you -- you are rooting
for the other guy.

15:49.119 --> 15:52.122
You told me to go
and be with Owen,

15:52.122 --> 15:54.334
and then you turned on me,

15:54.334 --> 15:56.376
and now
you are not on my side.

15:56.376 --> 15:57.537
And we both know
you don't like me,

15:57.537 --> 15:58.918
but you are stuck with me.

15:58.918 --> 16:02.882
So here I am
in a wedding gown

16:02.882 --> 16:05.465
on the happiest
fricking day of my life

16:05.465 --> 16:09.049
in a room with no family
and no help

16:09.049 --> 16:11.051
and no one on my side
but you.

16:11.051 --> 16:12.852
So what can you do for me?

16:12.852 --> 16:16.646
What can you do for me,
Meredith?

16:16.646 --> 16:18.688
[ Sighs ]

16:18.688 --> 16:20.520
You're me.

16:20.520 --> 16:22.022
What?

16:22.022 --> 16:24.734
You're me before Derek.

16:24.734 --> 16:26.236
I can be here for you.

16:26.236 --> 16:28.238
I know how to do this.

16:28.238 --> 16:30.780
I can be
a trusted sister for you.

16:30.780 --> 16:32.532
Just how do you
want to play this?

16:32.532 --> 16:34.614
Do you need me to tell you
you're a beautiful bride

16:34.614 --> 16:36.116
and kick your ass
down that aisle?

16:36.116 --> 16:37.997
You're a beautiful bride.

16:37.997 --> 16:40.170
Turn around.
I'll start kicking.

16:40.170 --> 16:42.672
Do you need me to call
your mother and yell at her?

16:42.672 --> 16:44.544
I'm your girl.

16:44.544 --> 16:47.387
If you need a shoulder
to cry on, I have two.

16:47.387 --> 16:49.759
If you want to freak out
and call it off,

16:49.759 --> 16:51.971
if you want to run,
I'll drive the getaway car.

16:54.264 --> 16:57.097
Just let me know
what you need.

16:57.097 --> 16:58.848
I'm here for you.

16:58.848 --> 17:01.941
I am your family, Amelia.

17:01.941 --> 17:05.405
Today, I am your person.

17:05.405 --> 17:07.647
Just tell me
what you want to do.

17:07.647 --> 17:09.819
[ Bells chiming,
thunder rumbles ]

17:14.534 --> 17:16.076
-What are you doing?
-We're running.

17:16.076 --> 17:19.209
Oh!

17:19.209 --> 17:21.501
-Where are we running?
-Doesn't matter. Let's go!

17:21.501 --> 17:23.663
Aah!

17:23.663 --> 17:26.716
♪♪

17:28.128 --> 17:30.130
Aah!

17:35.305 --> 17:37.307
Oh, God. So many people.
All those people!

17:37.307 --> 17:38.348
Okay, stop it.

17:38.348 --> 17:40.270
And the food!
Oh, my -- All that food.

17:40.270 --> 17:41.851
Stop. Don't do that.

17:41.851 --> 17:43.643
The food doesn't matter.

17:43.643 --> 17:45.275
Amelia's what matters.

17:45.275 --> 17:48.488
Right. Okay.
What happened?

17:48.488 --> 17:49.949
Nothing happened.

17:49.949 --> 17:50.860
What's wrong with Owen?

17:50.860 --> 17:53.323
Nothing's wrong with Owen.

17:53.323 --> 17:54.864
Well,
he could use some sun.

17:54.864 --> 17:56.116
[ Horn honks ]

17:56.116 --> 17:56.996
There's nothing
wrong with Owen.

17:56.996 --> 17:59.369
Then why are we doing this?

18:00.580 --> 18:02.372
Okay, so then
I hung up the phone,

18:02.372 --> 18:06.256
and I went over to
the table and [groans]

18:06.256 --> 18:07.167
What? Wha-- W-What?

18:07.167 --> 18:08.258
You -- You okay?

18:08.258 --> 18:09.509
Found it.

18:09.509 --> 18:10.880
[ Chuckles ]
[ Sighs ]

18:10.880 --> 18:12.132
All right, look.
Let's get out of here.

18:12.132 --> 18:15.265
Okay. Ah.

18:15.265 --> 18:17.096
Okay, you-- you're
having contractions.

18:17.096 --> 18:18.808
No.
Braxton-Hicks all day.

18:18.808 --> 18:19.719
Ben, I'm fine.
I'm fine.

18:19.719 --> 18:21.351
Mm-hmm. Go on. Sit down.
Come on. No.

18:21.351 --> 18:23.313
We got to get these rings
over to Owen, and I'm gonna --

18:23.313 --> 18:24.564
Kep-- Kepner -- Kepner,
have a seat.

18:24.564 --> 18:27.187
[ Groans ] Oh, boy.

18:27.187 --> 18:28.228
Okay, sitting sounds good.

18:28.228 --> 18:29.489
-Okay.
-It's good.

18:29.489 --> 18:30.570
[ Thunder rumbles ]

18:30.570 --> 18:33.653
So, I will repair
this tendon right here

18:33.653 --> 18:35.945
and get you sewn right up.

18:35.945 --> 18:37.827
I didn't know
you could do that.

18:37.827 --> 18:39.369
Are you a doctor?

18:39.369 --> 18:40.580
I am.

18:40.580 --> 18:43.243
Oh. I'm confused.

18:43.243 --> 18:44.414
That's okay.

18:44.414 --> 18:48.127
Um, Louise, do you
remember your son at all?

18:48.127 --> 18:48.958
Donnie?

18:48.958 --> 18:50.550
Son? Son? I...

18:50.550 --> 18:54.884
I don't -- I don't
have any children.

18:54.884 --> 18:56.556
Okay.

18:56.556 --> 18:58.888
Well, a-actually, you do.

18:58.888 --> 19:00.310
I'm having a baby?

19:00.310 --> 19:01.931
We're having a baby?

19:01.931 --> 19:03.313
Whoops. [ Clears throat ]
No, that's --

19:03.313 --> 19:04.224
That is not what I meant.

19:04.224 --> 19:06.186
We're having a baby.

19:07.937 --> 19:09.108
I can't wait.

19:09.108 --> 19:11.030
Mm-hmm.

19:11.030 --> 19:13.072
Uh, me neither.

19:14.444 --> 19:15.445
Congratulations.

19:15.445 --> 19:17.197
You're dismissed, Doctor.
[ Laughs ]

19:17.197 --> 19:20.039
All right.
[ Chuckles ]

19:20.039 --> 19:22.912
Avery's with the mom,
so I'll let him know

19:22.912 --> 19:24.334
her son pulled through.

19:24.334 --> 19:26.125
Page me when he wakes up.
Mm-hmm.

19:28.958 --> 19:30.340
How was she in there?

19:30.340 --> 19:31.921
Sh-- Uh, she's fine.

19:31.921 --> 19:34.464
Bailey, she's not fine.

19:34.464 --> 19:36.386
Sofia keeps asking me
why Mom's so sad,

19:36.386 --> 19:38.758
and she wouldn't even
go to Owen's wedding.

19:38.758 --> 19:40.430
I feel like
I should do something.

19:40.430 --> 19:42.222
Robbins, there's
nothing you can do.

19:42.222 --> 19:44.474
This isn't your
business anymore.

19:44.474 --> 19:46.516
I --
Now, look,
she lost her child.

19:46.516 --> 19:48.858
The woman she loved
moved across the country.

19:48.858 --> 19:50.570
So, no, she's not okay.

19:50.570 --> 19:54.274
The only thing you can do
is get okay with it yourself.

19:54.274 --> 19:56.486
[ Thunder rumbles ]

19:56.486 --> 19:59.489
It's over.
I had the love of my life,

19:59.489 --> 20:03.703
and I just -- pssh -- pushed
him away, and now he's gone.

20:03.703 --> 20:05.245
I lost him.

20:05.245 --> 20:06.916
Let's not overstate this.

20:06.916 --> 20:08.288
He's just
living at Meredith's.

20:08.288 --> 20:10.169
[ Sighs ] Steph,
you didn't see his face.

20:10.169 --> 20:13.383
He's gone.

20:13.383 --> 20:14.964
[ Bell dinging,
indistinct conversations ]

20:14.964 --> 20:16.926
Oh, God. I'm sorry.

20:16.926 --> 20:18.137
It's fine.

20:18.137 --> 20:19.679
I'm sorry.
He's not gone-gone.

20:19.679 --> 20:20.890
Kyle is gone-gone.

20:20.890 --> 20:22.762
Making it worse.

20:22.762 --> 20:25.305
Hey, can I get a cheeseburger,
rings to go please? Thanks.

20:25.305 --> 20:26.896
Uh, hey, DeLuca,
are you working?

20:26.896 --> 20:28.648
Ugh, I just got off
an 18-hour shift.

20:28.648 --> 20:31.771
I've been dreaming
of this cheeseburger and my bed.

20:31.771 --> 20:33.313
Wilson's your patient now.

20:33.313 --> 20:34.854
I'm gonna go home.
What?

20:34.854 --> 20:37.447
Make sure that she doesn't
drive or fall in a toilet

20:37.447 --> 20:40.159
or go anywhere near them.

20:40.159 --> 20:42.121
No, Dr. Edwards. Please.

20:44.123 --> 20:46.125
You don't have to stay.
I'm fine.

20:46.125 --> 20:49.168
♪♪

20:51.541 --> 20:52.922
Hey, could I get that
for here?

20:52.922 --> 20:55.675
Man: Sure.

20:55.675 --> 20:57.006
[ Thunder rumbles ]

20:57.006 --> 21:00.430
[ Indistinct conversations ]

21:00.430 --> 21:03.303
So, they're just gone?
All three of them?

21:03.303 --> 21:05.224
Yeah, it would
appear so, yeah.

21:05.224 --> 21:07.727
[ Sighs ] And they
didn't say anything?

21:07.727 --> 21:08.808
They did not.

21:08.808 --> 21:11.561
Now, l-l-let's
just stay calm.

21:11.561 --> 21:12.522
I'm calm.

21:12.522 --> 21:14.854
I'm sure there's
a good reason.

21:14.854 --> 21:15.855
They'll be back soon.

21:15.855 --> 21:17.897
Absolutely.

21:17.897 --> 21:21.321
Hey, could you ask Kepner
to come here for a moment?

21:21.321 --> 21:25.955
Right. Um, it seems
we've lost Kepner, too.

21:25.955 --> 21:26.956
[ Thunder rumbles ]

21:26.956 --> 21:28.458
Wha--?

21:28.458 --> 21:30.710
[ Breathing heavily ]

21:30.710 --> 21:32.412
Okay. Okay.

21:32.412 --> 21:34.173
Okay. Okay.
[ Groans ]

21:34.173 --> 21:35.675
See, that -- that one
came a lot faster.

21:35.675 --> 21:37.256
They're -- They're -- They're
a lot closer together now.

21:37.256 --> 21:38.628
Maybe we should take this
party on to the hospital.

21:38.628 --> 21:39.969
[ Sighs ]

21:39.969 --> 21:41.180
Wait, wait, wait,
w-wait, wait, Ben.

21:41.180 --> 21:42.632
Wait, wait, wait.

21:42.632 --> 21:44.924
I don't -- I don't want
to have this baby in your car.

21:44.924 --> 21:46.636
Neither do I.
We're going to the hospital.

21:46.636 --> 21:47.767
No. No, No.
Hey.

21:47.767 --> 21:49.058
Okay, but figure

21:49.058 --> 21:50.770
my contractions
are close together

21:50.770 --> 21:53.022
plus traffic
plus the rain

21:53.022 --> 21:54.273
plus, uh --
I don't know --

21:54.273 --> 21:55.274
a tree in the road?

21:55.274 --> 21:56.606
What, you're saying
that you --

21:56.606 --> 21:59.068
I'm saying that between
your car and this house

21:59.068 --> 22:01.491
with heat,
running water, blankets,

22:01.491 --> 22:03.242
um, I'll stay here.
Yeah.

22:03.242 --> 22:04.944
I'm gonna have this baby
right here.

22:04.944 --> 22:06.496
-April, no.
-Ben, come on.

22:06.496 --> 22:08.998
It's having a baby
at home.

22:08.998 --> 22:10.620
People have done it
in caves.

22:10.620 --> 22:13.162
My mom did it once
in a barn, I think.

22:13.162 --> 22:14.293
We can do this.

22:14.293 --> 22:15.455
We should just
get in the car.

22:15.455 --> 22:16.796
[ Groans ]
Oh, oh, oh.
It's -- Okay.

22:16.796 --> 22:18.588
Okay. Okay. Okay.
But you know what?

22:18.588 --> 22:20.630
I'm gon-- I'm gonna call
an ambulance, though.

22:20.630 --> 22:22.221
-Oh, oh, oh.
-Get us some help.

22:22.221 --> 22:23.383
Okay. [ Gasps ]

22:23.383 --> 22:24.464
[ Cellphone beeps ]

22:24.464 --> 22:25.725
I'm gonna have
a baby.

22:25.725 --> 22:27.517
[ Both chuckle ]
You're gonna have a baby.

22:27.517 --> 22:29.849
[ Exhales sharply ]
On Meredith's rug.

22:29.849 --> 22:30.970
Right on Meredith's rug.

22:30.970 --> 22:31.971
[ Laughs ]

22:31.971 --> 22:33.102
[ Thunder rumbles ]
Ohh.

22:38.608 --> 22:39.899
Is it happening?
Am I having the baby now?

22:39.899 --> 22:41.320
Okay, you need to relax.

22:41.320 --> 22:43.072
Oh, I wish you could stay.

22:43.072 --> 22:45.405
I'm gonna stay right here
by your side the entire time.

22:45.405 --> 22:47.076
When you wake up,
I'm gonna be right here.

22:47.076 --> 22:48.748
Oh, you promise?

22:48.748 --> 22:51.951
I love you.

22:51.951 --> 22:53.082
I love you.

22:53.082 --> 22:54.704
Okay.

22:54.704 --> 22:56.295
[ Sighs ]

22:56.295 --> 22:57.627
So weird.

22:57.627 --> 22:59.959
No one say anything,
please.

22:59.959 --> 23:01.631
[ Monitor beeps ]
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

23:01.631 --> 23:04.003
April:
Warren has called 911,

23:04.003 --> 23:06.095
but I might be
having the baby here,

23:06.095 --> 23:08.638
so, uh, just, you know,
get here, please.

23:08.638 --> 23:10.059
[ Cellphone clicks ]
[ Sighs ]

23:10.059 --> 23:11.431
Hey, y-you sure you
don't want to...
Oh!

23:11.431 --> 23:12.391
...lie down?

23:12.391 --> 23:13.683
No.
[ Groaning ]

23:13.683 --> 23:16.355
Oh. Uh, I wish I had
an epidural for you.

23:16.355 --> 23:17.316
Don't need it.

23:17.316 --> 23:19.649
I am conquering the pain
with my mind.

23:19.649 --> 23:20.780
[ Chuckling ]
You weren't kidding.

23:20.780 --> 23:23.152
You -- You know
how to have a baby.

23:25.364 --> 23:29.288
Okay, Ben, um,
maybe go wash your hands,

23:29.288 --> 23:31.290
'cause I need you
to give me an exam,

23:31.290 --> 23:32.742
because my water just broke.

23:32.742 --> 23:35.705
Okay. Okay.

23:35.705 --> 23:38.838
You-- You're probably gonna see
my vagina, which might be weird.

23:38.838 --> 23:39.919
Yeah, but, uh, you know,
I'm a doctor,

23:39.919 --> 23:41.090
so, you know, it's all good.

23:41.090 --> 23:42.131
Okay. Right.

23:42.131 --> 23:43.963
[ Breathes heavily ]

23:43.963 --> 23:45.965
Meredith:
Tap it and let it settle
and then tap it some more.

23:45.965 --> 23:47.467
You get more that way.

23:47.467 --> 23:50.009
Why am I doing this?

23:50.009 --> 23:52.391
Why did you
make me do this?

23:52.391 --> 23:54.263
Why the hell would
you make me run?

23:54.263 --> 23:56.055
I didn't make you run.
You wanted to run.

23:56.055 --> 23:57.517
You dangled the carrot.

23:57.517 --> 23:59.559
You -- You dangled it
because you didn't want

23:59.559 --> 24:01.060
this wedding to happen,
so you dangled.

24:01.060 --> 24:02.652
I didn't
dangle anything.

24:02.652 --> 24:04.193
You're not a victim here.

24:04.193 --> 24:06.325
I presented you
with a menu of options.

24:06.325 --> 24:07.987
You chose to run.

24:07.987 --> 24:09.909
You wanted to run.

24:09.909 --> 24:11.571
You're right. You're right.

24:11.571 --> 24:13.162
[ Breathing heavily ]

24:13.162 --> 24:16.285
Why am I marrying Owen?

24:16.285 --> 24:17.917
Is my family right?

24:17.917 --> 24:19.839
Is this just one more
in a long line

24:19.839 --> 24:21.460
of ill-advised,
impulsive decisions?

24:21.460 --> 24:22.461
I don't even know.

24:22.461 --> 24:23.422
Shouldn't I know?

24:23.422 --> 24:25.635
Shouldn't I know
on my wedding day?

24:25.635 --> 24:26.425
[ Door chimes ]
Probably.

24:26.425 --> 24:28.217
Mer.

24:28.217 --> 24:31.591
I mean, what if I'm just --
What if Owen is my new drug

24:31.591 --> 24:33.432
and I'm just using him
to ignore the fact that...

24:33.432 --> 24:35.555
[ Cash register beeps
in distance ]

24:35.555 --> 24:36.936
That what?

24:36.936 --> 24:38.227
That Mer's right,
that Owen's had

24:38.227 --> 24:39.599
the love of his life
and so have I,

24:39.599 --> 24:41.100
and once it's gone,
everything else is just filler

24:41.100 --> 24:42.982
and you'll never, ever
have that feeling again.

24:42.982 --> 24:43.943
I mean, who gets that twice?

24:46.866 --> 24:48.988
Some of us would like
to have it once.

24:48.988 --> 24:52.031
♪♪

24:55.575 --> 25:00.499
So, he just kept asking me
to marry him again and again.

25:00.499 --> 25:03.382
I just couldn't say nothing
anymore, you know,

25:03.382 --> 25:06.215
so I just...
I just said no.
Man: Hey, get you guys
another round?

25:06.215 --> 25:07.757
[ Bell dinging,
indistinct conversations ]

25:07.757 --> 25:08.888
You could've said yes.

25:08.888 --> 25:10.259
Here you go.

25:12.091 --> 25:12.972
I should go home.

25:12.972 --> 25:14.684
I need to go home.

25:14.684 --> 25:15.725
What? Whoa.
No, no, no, no, no.

25:15.725 --> 25:17.266
You cannot drive home.

25:17.266 --> 25:19.518
No, stupid,
I'm gonna call.

25:19.518 --> 25:22.602
I'm looking for my phone
to call a Goober.

25:22.602 --> 25:23.733
[ Sighs ]

25:23.733 --> 25:24.944
I can't marry him.

25:24.944 --> 25:27.026
I want to,
but I can't marry anyone.

25:27.026 --> 25:28.357
Why's that?

25:28.357 --> 25:29.739
Just 'cause --
none of your business.

25:29.739 --> 25:31.360
Okay. Right. Sorry.

25:31.360 --> 25:34.363
God, where is my --
Oh, my God!

25:34.363 --> 25:36.245
What?

25:36.245 --> 25:38.367
This isn't even my purse.
[ Sighs ]

25:38.367 --> 25:39.869
Man: Yeah,
what can I get you?

25:39.869 --> 25:44.624
I can't marry him
because I'm already married.

25:44.624 --> 25:47.086
♪♪

25:48.718 --> 25:50.630
[ Groaning ]

25:50.630 --> 25:51.631
[ Grunts ]

25:51.631 --> 25:52.722
Okay, okay.

25:52.722 --> 25:53.723
It's done. Go.
Do it.

25:53.723 --> 25:55.434
Okay, you just relax,
all right?

25:55.434 --> 25:58.017
You know the drill.

25:58.017 --> 25:59.348
You're gonna
feel my hand...

25:59.348 --> 26:00.680
Okay.

26:00.680 --> 26:03.232
[ Breathing heavily ]

26:06.065 --> 26:08.237
[ Sighs ]

26:08.237 --> 26:09.989
Okay, Warren,
let's wrap it up.

26:09.989 --> 26:12.111
Sorry. I just --
I-I -- I can't --

26:12.111 --> 26:13.653
I don't know what I'm --

26:13.653 --> 26:15.494
Come on. You've done
a pelvic before, haven't you?

26:15.494 --> 26:17.116
Yeah, plenty, plenty,
but t-this doesn't feel right.

26:17.116 --> 26:18.247
Don't tell me
it doesn't feel right.

26:18.247 --> 26:19.659
It's my freaking cervix.

26:19.659 --> 26:21.370
Just check how dilated it is,
and get out of my va--

26:21.370 --> 26:24.163
A-April, April,

26:24.163 --> 26:26.045
it's a foot.

26:26.045 --> 26:28.007
I feel a foot.

26:29.508 --> 26:31.300
No.

26:31.300 --> 26:33.172
It's breech.

26:33.172 --> 26:34.553
It's a footling breech.

26:34.553 --> 26:35.925
[ Gasps ]

26:35.925 --> 26:37.637
Okay. Okay.

26:37.637 --> 26:39.178
And -- And I feel the cord.

26:39.178 --> 26:40.389
Wha--?
[ Breathing heavily ]

26:40.389 --> 26:42.431
No. No.

26:42.431 --> 26:44.894
Is -- Is there a pulse?

26:46.776 --> 26:47.777
Answer me!

26:47.777 --> 26:49.358
I don't think so, no.

26:49.358 --> 26:50.149
No.

26:50.149 --> 26:51.490
[ Thunder rumbling ]

26:51.490 --> 26:53.863
[ Water sloshes ]

26:53.863 --> 26:55.534
So my baby's gonna die?

26:55.534 --> 26:57.446
No. No, April. No.

26:57.446 --> 26:58.577
No, it just means
that it's not getting

26:58.577 --> 27:00.499
all the blood that it could be
and that --

27:00.499 --> 27:02.161
that we have to get the baby out
as fast as possible

27:02.161 --> 27:03.452
so we can get
the pressure off the cord.

27:03.452 --> 27:06.335
Okay. [ Breathes deeply ]
Okay.

27:06.335 --> 27:09.128
So I need a C-section
soon as possible.

27:09.128 --> 27:10.800
Yes. Yes.

27:10.800 --> 27:12.091
Okay, okay, okay.

27:12.091 --> 27:12.842
[ Breathes deeply ]

27:12.842 --> 27:15.594
Okay, um...

27:15.594 --> 27:18.808
So...okay.

27:18.808 --> 27:21.470
So...

27:21.470 --> 27:23.763
The light is better
in the kitchen.

27:23.763 --> 27:26.265
What? Wait, wait, wait.
No. No. No.

27:26.265 --> 27:27.897
I'm not giving you
a C-section.

27:27.897 --> 27:29.188
Look, there's
an ambulance coming.

27:29.188 --> 27:30.860
Ben, we both know
it doesn't matter.

27:30.860 --> 27:32.271
I'm not doing it. I can't.

27:32.271 --> 27:33.482
[ Stammers ]

27:33.482 --> 27:34.824
We'll get you
to the hospital.

27:34.824 --> 27:36.535
My baby is dying,
its blood supply is cut off,

27:36.535 --> 27:38.277
and it's going to die.

27:38.277 --> 27:39.578
There is an ambulance
coming!

27:39.578 --> 27:41.620
Ben! Ben!

27:41.620 --> 27:44.744
Even if they were here now,
they can't help me.

27:44.744 --> 27:45.745
You can.

27:45.745 --> 27:47.046
I-It's coming.
It's coming.

27:47.046 --> 27:48.998
[ Groaning ]

27:50.920 --> 27:52.752
[ Thunder rumbles ]

27:52.752 --> 27:54.924
[ Grunts, groaning ]

27:54.924 --> 27:56.966
Come on.

27:56.966 --> 27:58.637
[ Grunts ]

27:58.637 --> 28:00.970
[ Screaming ]

28:00.970 --> 28:02.301
♪♪

28:08.107 --> 28:09.268
[ Cellphone rings, beeps ]
Okay, I know, Ben.

28:09.268 --> 28:10.980
I know. I'm coming.
I got held --

28:10.980 --> 28:13.733
♪♪

28:18.908 --> 28:20.409
[ Sighs ]

28:20.409 --> 28:25.164
Well, um, on the plus side,
um, you're well-liked.

28:25.164 --> 28:26.585
A lot of people came.

28:26.585 --> 28:28.417
And nobody wants
to rush you.

28:28.417 --> 28:29.959
They just want to know
what's gonna happen.

28:29.959 --> 28:31.090
What do you think?

28:31.090 --> 28:32.832
Here's what I think,
Karev.

28:32.832 --> 28:34.213
I think
if you get to the point

28:34.213 --> 28:36.175
where you're gonna walk
down the aisle with someone,

28:36.175 --> 28:41.510
she's earned some trust...
and faith.

28:41.510 --> 28:44.974
She's earned
the benefit of the doubt.

28:44.974 --> 28:46.435
So I'm giving it to her.

28:46.435 --> 28:48.607
She deserves that.

28:48.607 --> 28:50.349
You're right.

28:50.349 --> 28:53.352
You're absolutely right.

28:53.352 --> 28:55.775
[ Sighs ]

28:55.775 --> 28:57.356
[ Sighs ]

29:00.659 --> 29:02.741
[ Slurping ]

29:05.034 --> 29:07.166
Are we going in?

29:07.166 --> 29:08.247
Why are you
looking at me?

29:12.331 --> 29:14.373
Amelia?

29:14.373 --> 29:16.635
I don't know.

29:16.635 --> 29:18.637
If we don't go in,
where would we go?

29:20.219 --> 29:21.801
Why's everybody
asking me?

29:21.801 --> 29:23.052
Come on, Mer.

29:23.052 --> 29:24.804
What do I know
about getting married?

29:24.804 --> 29:27.386
And who am I to say we only get
one great love in our life?

29:27.386 --> 29:29.728
Lots of people get two.

29:29.728 --> 29:30.810
Look at...

29:30.810 --> 29:32.311
[ Woman vocalizing ]

29:34.313 --> 29:35.484
Look at...

29:35.484 --> 29:36.565
Well, I don't know.

29:36.565 --> 29:38.027
I can't think of any
right now, but --

29:38.027 --> 29:40.109
-Richard Webber.
-Yes! Exactly. Thank you.

29:40.109 --> 29:42.031
Richard Webber. Exactly.
You see?

29:42.031 --> 29:43.242
Maybe we get two,

29:43.242 --> 29:45.454
maybe we get 11,
maybe we get 30.

29:45.454 --> 29:47.366
Isn't that better,
just to believe that?

29:47.366 --> 29:48.787
Yeah.

29:48.787 --> 29:50.619
I mean, Owen believes it.

29:50.619 --> 29:51.790
I swear he does.

29:51.790 --> 29:53.172
And he loves you.

29:53.172 --> 29:55.124
So maybe this time
is different for you.

29:55.124 --> 29:58.467
Maybe this time,
you're right.

29:58.467 --> 30:00.880
♪♪

30:03.973 --> 30:06.475
[ Thunder rumbling ]

30:08.807 --> 30:10.099
All right, now, listen.

30:10.099 --> 30:11.520
There's no anesthesia.

30:11.520 --> 30:13.602
Ice is all we got,
so the pain's gonna --

30:14.934 --> 30:16.525
The pain's gonna be bad.

30:16.525 --> 30:19.278
Okay. All right?
Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

30:19.278 --> 30:20.900
Okay.

30:20.900 --> 30:23.112
Why is she at Meredith's?
I got to get my keys.

30:23.112 --> 30:24.653
Oh --
No, no. There's no time.

30:24.653 --> 30:26.155
Here.

30:26.155 --> 30:27.786
Right. You rotate the baby
in utero -- face down.

30:27.786 --> 30:30.409
No, I know. The position will
look different than you've seen.

30:30.409 --> 30:31.500
Okay.
Is she okay?

30:31.500 --> 30:33.162
[ Cellphone beeps ]
April? April?

30:33.162 --> 30:34.503
Hey, April?
Can she hear me?

30:34.503 --> 30:35.414
Jackson, Jackson!

30:35.414 --> 30:36.335
Jackson, I'm here.

30:36.335 --> 30:37.626
Okay, okay,
I'm right here.

30:37.626 --> 30:40.169
Okay? I'm right here.
Okay. Okay. Okay. Okay.

30:40.169 --> 30:41.670
Ha! Jackpot!

30:41.670 --> 30:43.052
What?
It's an old medical bag.

30:43.052 --> 30:44.763
It must've been her mom's.
[ Groans ]

30:44.763 --> 30:48.597
There's some gauze
and, uh -- ha-ha! -- a scalpel.

30:50.930 --> 30:52.141
And some lidocaine?

30:52.141 --> 30:53.642
No.

30:53.642 --> 30:54.853
Hey, Warren, what do you have
to pack her with?

30:54.853 --> 30:56.025
Uh...

30:56.025 --> 30:58.437
[ Breathing heavily ]

30:58.437 --> 31:00.689
...dish towels.

31:01.860 --> 31:04.153
Okay.

31:04.904 --> 31:06.485
Can you feel that?

31:06.485 --> 31:07.907
Yeah.

31:07.907 --> 31:09.989
[ Breathing heavily ]

31:11.540 --> 31:14.333
Okay, Ben, I need you to
promise me something, okay?

31:14.333 --> 31:16.755
Yeah.
If you feel like
you're gonna lose me,

31:16.755 --> 31:18.377
if I'm bleeding out, you...
No.

31:18.377 --> 31:20.419
...you make sure
that this baby is okay.

31:20.419 --> 31:21.670
Oh, no, no, no.

31:21.670 --> 31:23.963
April, do not --
Ben, don't listen to her, okay?

31:23.963 --> 31:26.465
You save her.
You save both of them.

31:26.465 --> 31:30.559
You promise me that you will
save this baby, no matter what.

31:30.559 --> 31:32.101
Ben, okay?!

31:32.101 --> 31:33.392
Arizona:
Warren, you have got this.
No!

31:33.392 --> 31:34.473
You have got them both.

31:34.473 --> 31:36.065
Ben, please. Okay?
[ Groans ]

31:36.065 --> 31:39.108
Everybody, just quiet!
Please.

31:39.108 --> 31:40.779
[ Breathes deeply ]

31:41.981 --> 31:43.482
Miranda?

31:43.482 --> 31:44.984
Yes?

31:46.575 --> 31:49.238
I want to do this,
all right?

31:49.238 --> 31:51.580
I-I have to do this,
all right?

31:51.580 --> 31:52.911
I know.

31:52.911 --> 31:54.703
Ben, w-- d-don't hang up.

31:54.703 --> 31:56.745
I trust you.

31:56.745 --> 32:00.169
♪♪

32:08.717 --> 32:10.889
[ Breathing heavily ]

32:10.889 --> 32:13.142
Okay. Okay.

32:18.978 --> 32:21.981
[ Screaming ]

32:24.523 --> 32:26.945
Okay, hey, hey.

32:28.988 --> 32:30.990
[ Screaming stops ]
What's happening?

32:37.706 --> 32:39.288
April, please?

32:39.288 --> 32:40.959
[ Siren wailing ]

32:43.082 --> 32:45.134
Say something. Ben?

32:50.639 --> 32:53.432
[ Alessia Cara's
"River of Tears" plays ]

32:59.438 --> 33:03.862
♪ Still got the flowers
that you sent ♪

33:03.862 --> 33:05.524
♪ And the note you wrote ♪

33:05.524 --> 33:10.279
♪ That said that we were
meant to be forever ♪

33:10.279 --> 33:14.243
♪ I keep them all as evidence ♪

33:14.243 --> 33:17.076
♪ In a drawer under the mirror ♪

33:17.076 --> 33:20.499
♪ Filled with empty promises ♪

33:20.499 --> 33:25.714
♪ I don't know why
I keep letting you lie to me ♪

33:25.714 --> 33:30.299
♪ Hard as I try,
it seems I can't break away ♪

33:30.299 --> 33:33.052
♪ I thought that
you would be the hero ♪

33:33.052 --> 33:34.893
♪ Come and save the day ♪

33:34.893 --> 33:36.895
♪ But you're a villain ♪

33:36.895 --> 33:40.349
♪ Your sins unforgiven ♪

33:40.349 --> 33:44.563
♪ I'm going down, and you
have watched me drown... ♪

33:44.563 --> 33:45.904
Oh, oh, oh.
Hey, hey, hey.

33:45.904 --> 33:47.946
♪ ...in a river of tears... ♪
Okay, come on.

33:47.946 --> 33:49.858
Come on, now.
♪ ...lost in the stream ♪

33:49.858 --> 33:52.111
Okay. Here we go.
Bedtime.

33:52.111 --> 33:53.112
♪ Under the waves, I've found
the strength to say... ♪
[ Groans ]

33:53.112 --> 33:55.704
Let me get you
some water, okay?

33:55.704 --> 33:58.617
♪ ...the river of tears... ♪
I was living in my car.

33:58.617 --> 33:59.998
♪ ...has washed me clean ♪
Did you know that
I lived in my car?

33:59.998 --> 34:01.039
Whoa, whoa. Hey, hey.

34:01.039 --> 34:03.122
Where are you going?
Whoa.

34:03.122 --> 34:04.963
♪ Go 'head and wish me well ♪
And then I met him,

34:04.963 --> 34:07.126
and I wasn't living
in my car anymore.
♪ I'll cry a wishing well ♪

34:07.126 --> 34:09.218
Everybody loved him.

34:09.218 --> 34:11.380
♪ I'll cry a wishing well ♪
I did.

34:11.380 --> 34:12.761
W-What are you --
What are you doing?
♪ I'll cry a wishing well ♪

34:12.761 --> 34:14.723
I'm gonna go --
I'm gonna go to bed.

34:14.723 --> 34:16.805
♪ I'll fly before I fail ♪
Okay. Um, I-I-I should go.

34:16.805 --> 34:18.557
♪ I'll set sail and drift away ♪
Okay, you're --
you're good, right?

34:18.557 --> 34:20.229
Never wanted anyone
to stop loving him.

34:20.229 --> 34:22.941
♪ So I won't need you here ♪

34:22.941 --> 34:24.523
[ Voice breaking ] So if I...
♪ Love sinks and hope floats ♪

34:24.523 --> 34:26.105
...I bought the wrong something,
he would...

34:26.105 --> 34:28.527
♪ In a river of tears ♪

34:28.527 --> 34:31.400
♪ In a river of tears ♪
...he would hit me in my face.

34:31.400 --> 34:32.821
♪ Cry me a river,
build myself a bridge ♪
Hey.

34:32.821 --> 34:34.243
Or my stomach. Or...

34:34.243 --> 34:36.115
♪ I'm over this ♪

34:36.115 --> 34:38.697
♪ Can't let memories become
the death of me ♪
Nobody knew that but me.

34:38.697 --> 34:40.459
[ Sniffles ]

34:40.459 --> 34:44.042
♪ I'm glad to see
everything that you are ♪
So -- So I ran.

34:44.042 --> 34:45.544
I had to make sure
he would never find me.

34:45.544 --> 34:48.207
♪ And I believe that
you are everything I needed ♪

34:48.207 --> 34:49.468
And if you try
to divorce him...

34:49.468 --> 34:51.009
♪ But I don't need no more ♪
[ Crying ]

34:51.009 --> 34:53.091
♪ I'm going down, and you
have watched me drown... ♪

34:53.091 --> 34:56.094
He would find me.

34:56.094 --> 34:58.927
♪ ...in a river of tears... ♪
Does Karev know
about any of this?

34:58.927 --> 35:00.349
♪ ...lost beneath the stream ♪
No. No.

35:00.349 --> 35:02.521
Alex would try and protect me,
but he can't.

35:02.521 --> 35:05.814
♪ Under the waves, I've found
the strength to say... ♪

35:05.814 --> 35:07.356
He doesn't even know
my real name.

35:07.356 --> 35:08.987
♪ ...the river of tears
has washed me clean ♪

35:08.987 --> 35:09.898
You should tell him.

35:09.898 --> 35:11.069
He'll understand.

35:11.069 --> 35:12.491
Karev's a really -- Hey.

35:12.491 --> 35:14.032
Okay, hey, don't.

35:14.032 --> 35:15.864
♪ Go 'head and wish me well ♪
Okay, don't do that, okay?

35:15.864 --> 35:17.826
Let's get you into
you bed, all right?
♪ I'll cry a wishing well ♪

35:17.826 --> 35:19.238
No, no. Stop.

35:19.238 --> 35:20.159
[ Laughs ]

35:20.159 --> 35:21.620
♪ I'll fly before I fail ♪

35:21.620 --> 35:24.203
♪ I'll set sail and drift away ♪

35:24.203 --> 35:27.166
♪ So I won't need you here ♪

35:27.166 --> 35:31.510
Okay, no. No.
♪ Love sinks and hope floats
in a river of tears ♪

35:31.510 --> 35:33.172
Dr. Karev, hold on.

35:33.172 --> 35:34.303
Okay, hey!
What are you --
♪ In a river of tears ♪

35:34.303 --> 35:36.305
Jo: Alex!

35:36.305 --> 35:38.177
Alex!

35:38.177 --> 35:40.639
[ Thunder rumbles ]

35:41.720 --> 35:42.891
[ Sighs ]

35:42.891 --> 35:44.393
[ Door opens ]

35:44.393 --> 35:46.765
Hey. What are
you doing here?

35:46.765 --> 35:48.977
[ Door closes ]
They asked me
to give you this.

35:48.977 --> 35:50.399
W-- Kepner's the --

35:50.399 --> 35:52.321
Well, she forgot
the rings at Meredith's,

35:52.321 --> 35:55.694
and then everything
went sideways and...

35:55.694 --> 35:56.825
it's a girl.

35:56.825 --> 35:58.697
She had the baby?
[ Chuckling ] Yeah.

35:58.697 --> 36:03.452
Some -- Well, I know you'll hear
about it, but, anyway, here.

36:03.452 --> 36:05.204
Thanks.

36:06.995 --> 36:08.627
You know, you didn't
have to do this.

36:08.627 --> 36:10.959
I know.

36:10.959 --> 36:11.840
[ Thunder rumbles ]

36:11.840 --> 36:14.052
It's funny. Um...

36:14.052 --> 36:15.294
[ Sighs ]
The way things are going,

36:15.294 --> 36:17.095
I'm not sure
Amelia and I are --

36:17.095 --> 36:18.507
[ Door opens ]

36:18.507 --> 36:20.178
Meredith: Hey.
Hey.

36:20.178 --> 36:21.680
She's back.
-Where is she?

36:21.680 --> 36:23.181
No, she doesn't want
to see you now.

36:23.181 --> 36:24.393
What?
Before the ceremony --

36:24.393 --> 36:25.684
it's bad luck.

36:25.684 --> 36:27.396
Hurry up and get in there.
[ Breathes sharply ]

36:27.396 --> 36:28.937
I mean,
she needs 10 minutes.

36:28.937 --> 36:30.439
Okay. All right.
All right.

36:30.439 --> 36:32.521
Okay. All right.

36:32.521 --> 36:34.443
Hey, um...

36:34.443 --> 36:35.944
Happy for you, man.

36:35.944 --> 36:37.776
Thanks.

36:37.776 --> 36:40.028
Oh, hey, um...

36:40.028 --> 36:41.820
there'll be food after.

36:41.820 --> 36:43.452
[ Thunder rumbles ]

36:43.452 --> 36:46.375
[ Door closes ]

36:46.375 --> 36:48.957
So, are you staying, then?

36:50.168 --> 36:52.251
I might.

36:53.091 --> 36:54.293
Yeah, I mean,
I like a wedding.

36:54.293 --> 36:55.544
[ Chuckles ]

36:55.544 --> 36:58.176
It's funny. Owen was
supposed to be my best man.

37:01.390 --> 37:04.513
Anyway, what about you?
Did you have a big wedding?

37:04.513 --> 37:06.054
No.

37:06.054 --> 37:10.309
We wrote our vows on a...
on a Post-it note.

37:10.309 --> 37:12.190
[ Chuckles ]

37:12.190 --> 37:14.273
He was afraid
of commitment?

37:14.273 --> 37:16.315
No, just the opposite --
It was me.

37:16.315 --> 37:19.278
He loved me so much,
he didn't care.

37:19.278 --> 37:20.489
Poor guy.

37:20.489 --> 37:23.201
[ Chuckling ] I barely
gave him a wedding.

37:25.454 --> 37:27.326
What'd you give him?

37:27.326 --> 37:29.127
We went to City Hall.

37:29.127 --> 37:30.579
Just the two of us.

